## 🔒 **2. Pisah login endpoint antara Web dan Mobile (lebih aman & bersih)**

Nah ini yang paling direkomendasikan buat sistem kayak punya lo, karena:

* Super admin (web) dan user mobile (employee/manager/finance) **beda jalur akses**.
* Token bisa punya **scope/guard** berbeda.
* Lo bisa kasih middleware berbeda (`auth:web_admin` vs `auth:api`).

Contoh:

```
POST /api/v1/admin/login     → buat web super admin
POST /api/v1/mobile/login    → buat mobile user (employee/manager/finance)
```

### di `AdminAuthController`:

```php
public function login(Request $request)
{
    $credentials = $request->only('email', 'password');
    if (!Auth::attempt($credentials)) {
        return response()->json(['message' => 'Invalid credentials'], 401);
    }

    $user = Auth::user();

    if ($user->role !== 'super_admin') {
        return response()->json(['message' => 'Access denied'], 403);
    }

    $token = $user->createToken('web_admin_token', ['web'])->plainTextToken;

    return response()->json([
        'token' => $token,
        'user' => $user,
        'message' => 'Welcome Super Admin!',
    ]);
}
```

### di `MobileAuthController`:

```php
public function login(Request $request)
{
    $credentials = $request->only('email', 'password');
    if (!Auth::attempt($credentials)) {
        return response()->json(['message' => 'Invalid credentials'], 401);
    }

    $user = Auth::user();

    if (!in_array($user->role, ['employee', 'manager', 'finance'])) {
        return response()->json(['message' => 'Access denied'], 403);
    }

    $token = $user->createToken('mobile_token', ['mobile'])->plainTextToken;

    return response()->json([
        'token' => $token,
        'role' => $user->role,
        'user' => $user,
    ]);
}
```

🧠 Sekarang token lo bisa beda scope:

* Web admin → token dengan `['web']`
* Mobile → token dengan `['mobile']`

Itu artinya nanti di middleware lo bisa ngebatesin akses:

```php
if (!$request->user()->tokenCan('mobile')) {
    abort(403, 'Invalid token type');
}
```

